TodoList - React/Next.js To-Do List Application
A simple and functional To-Do list application built with React and TypeScript, styled using Tailwind CSS and custom components.

Features
- Add, edit, complete and delete tasks.
- Filter tasks by All, Active or Completed.
- Persistent storage using `localStorage`.
- Dark mode support via Tailwind CSS configuration.
- Responsive design with accessible UI elements.
- Smooth animations for task interactions.
- Toast notifications for user feedback.

Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   bash
2. git clone https://github.com/Andreja651/To-Do-List-Web-App
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
CopyEdit
cd todoapp
3. Install dependencies:
bash
CopyEdit
npm install
4. Run the development server:
bash
CopyEdit
npm run dev
5. Open your browser and visit http://localhost:3000 to see the app in action.
6. https://lovable.dev/projects/7b5dc1c9-342a-4d2f-915c-bcbdd506d393?magic_link=mc_11566ea9-cec9-48b8-ab2d-6c7d51ea2165

Project Structure
• ToDoList: Main component managing the todo state and logic.
• TodoInput: Input form component for adding new tasks.
• TodoFilters: Component for filtering tasks.
• TodoList: Renders the list of todos with edit, delete, and toggle functionality.
• Card: UI container with shadow and border styles.
• useToast: Hook for toast notifications.

Technologies Used
• React with TypeScript
• Tailwind CSS with custom theming
• lucide-react icons
• class-variance-authority for component styling variants

Notes
• Tasks are stored in localStorage and loaded on app start.
• Unique IDs are generated with crypto.randomUUID().
• Graceful error handling on localStorage data retrieval.
